24], [22, 26], [22, 28], [22, 30]]}, "lines": {"text": ["Share the appointment details with the person you are", "Step 4:", "helping.", "\u2022 Make sure to write down the details, including the booking number, the date, time and location.", "\u2022 Remind the person not to arrive more than 10 minutes before their appointment.", "Offer to help them make their transportation plan to get", "Step 5:", "to and from the clinic (more details below).", "Transportation to and from the clinic", "\u2022 Once an appointment date and time is set, make your transportation plan with a family member,", "a friend, or with OC Transpo or Para Transpo.", "\u2022 If none of these options are available, a free transportation service is available for people in", "need.", "\u2022 Call 2-1-1 or register online with VaxAide.ca, or by dialing 613-869-8221 to set up the ride", "once you have your booking number. A volunteer will follow-up to confirm. service", "\u2022 Please call at least 48 hours before your appointment.", "Language accessibility:", "\u2022 Both the Province of Ontario and OPH offer multilingual booking support over the phone in", "languages other than French and English.", "\u2022 For callers who are Deaf or hearing-impaired, please call Telehealth Ontario TTY at 1-866-797-", "0007 to book through the provincial booking line. If you do not have a Health Card, you can call", "OPH VRS (613-580-2400) or TTY (613-580-2401) to book your appointment over the phone.", "How to book a COVID-19 vaccine appointment for someone else | Ottawa Public Health (02/06/2021) 2"], "bbox": [[0.193524, 0.076909, 0.6738959999999999, 0.022513], [0.088235, 0.074577, 0.098009, 0.025391], [0.198636, 0.102965, 0.099988, 0.022513], [0.088235, 0.132647, 0.85035, 0.016927], [0.088235, 0.151587, 0.7229030000000001, 0.016927], [0.193524, 0.187969, 0.6870809999999999, 0.022513], [0.088235, 0.185638, 0.098009, 0.025391], [0.19861, 0.214025, 0.531369, 0.022513], [0.08822, 0.269321, 0.45582799999999996, 0.0225